 of art history, cultural studies, aesthetics, film studies, along with the political agendas that motivate them in feminism, gender and queer theory, as well as identity politics more generally.  afunded by Humboldt-Universität zu Berlin  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aAlterity. 4aArt. 4aCultural Studies. 4aFine Arts. 4aGaze. 4aIdentity. 4aImage. 4aTheory of Art. 4aVisual Culture. 4aVisual Studies. 7aART / History / General.2bisacsh  aAlterity.  aArt.  aCultural Studies.  aFine Arts.  aGaze.  aIdentity.  aImage.  aTheory of Art.  aVisual Culture.  aVisual Studies.2 aHumboldt-Universität zu Berlinefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2020z9783110704655oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z97831106896170 cprintz978383765352640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839453520?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839453520zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839453520/ori